Theming / Colors:

Primary, secondary, accent colors, and text colors should be configurable via the JSON or a separate theme.json

Default colors should resemble BrittanyChiang.com (dark background, bright accent, light text)

Components / Pages:

Header with navigation links

Hero section with name, tagline, and call-to-action buttons

About section

Projects section with images, titles, descriptions, links, and optional GitHub/Live Demo buttons

Skills section with categories and skill levels

Work experience & education

Contact section with a form (submission can be placeholder)

Footer with social links

Bonus / Nice-to-have:

Smooth scrolling to sections

Mobile navigation drawer or hamburger menu

Animated skill bars or tech icons

Optional dark/light mode toggle

README.md:

Include detailed instructions for a senior React dev who is new to Next.js

Sections to include: Project Overview, Installation, Running Locally, Folder Structure, Data Configuration, Color/Theming, Deployment (Vercel recommended), Customization Tips

Provide example commands for dev and prod environments

